<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OSTLER-COLUMN-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FLORIDA'S NEW ROLE MODEL _ TEXAS
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     By SCOTT OSTLER 
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &LR;   &LR;  SAN FRANCISCO _ Down in Florida, where executing condemned
prisoners is a mom 'n' pop operation, the state Legislature just
voted to offer an alternative to Old Sparky, the electric chair.
<P>
   Old Sparky has never quite achieved UL-approved status.
Sometimes the chair works OK, other times it causes blue flames to
shoot out of the victim's skull, which is acceptable, really, only
on the Fourth of July.
</P>
<P>
   The Legislature decided to let prisoners choose lethal
injection. Yep, they can trade Old Sparky for Old Rusty.
</P>
<P>
   ``What I hope is that we become more like Texas,'' said Brad
Thomas, the governor's policy adviser on the death penalty. ``Bring
in the witnesses, put them on the gurney, and let's rock 'n'
roll.''
</P>
<P>
   So apparently they're going to execute the witnesses, too. Had
they done that all along, there wouldn't have been anyone around to
gripe about Old Sparky.
</P>
<P>
   STILL TRICKLING IN: The bitter and desperate pleas of the folks
who belong to what might be called the Flat Millennium Society.
</P>
<P>
   The New Millennium, they point out, is still a year away; it
starts the first day of 2001. I thought the worldwide millennium
celebration would suck the wind out of these people's sails, but
no.
</P>
<P>
   Here's the deal, you 2001ers: Technically, logically,
mathematically, this is the last year of the old millennium. We all
know that. But we don't care. We couldn't wait. We were sick of the
old millennium. Many of us wanted to start the new millennium in
1973, but with the aid of medication we were able to relax and wait
for a round number.
</P>
<P>
   LOST ARTS of the 20th Century Dept.: One recent evening, a man
rushed into the neckwear department of the downtown Macy's. He was
fully dressed in tux and was waving a black ribbon of some kind.
</P>
<P>
   ``Can anyone help me tie my tie?'' he pleaded. ``I've been
trying for an hour.''
</P>
<P>
   Several salespeople huddled, fiddled, twisted and finally
produced,  &UR; voila,  &LR; a long, twisted black ribbon.
</P>
<P>
   They sent the man to men's suits on the fourth floor, where
salesperson David whipped the bow tie into a neat &AMP; natty knot,
natch.
</P>
<P>
   It's a shame that such basic sartorial skills have been lost by
the microwave generation.
</P>
<P>
   Not that I'm preaching. I fasten my French cuffs with a stapler.
</P>
<P>
   DARYL GLEN CLIPPED a Y2K news story reporting that ``by early
afternoon a string of minor irritants was building up, from
software glitches that caused problems for Internet banking
customers to an Italian error which added a century onto some jail
sentences.''
</P>
<P>
   CARMEL HELL: From the Carmel Valley Pine Cone's police blotter:
``Report of bongo drums being played on the beach.''
</P>
<P>
   May a Y2K glitch add a century to this nervy lout's sentence.
</P>
<P>
   HEY, SHERRY Davis: Thanks for seven fine seasons at the Giants'
PA mike.
</P>
<P>
   And thanks to Sherry and the Giants for ignoring the indignant
cries of the manlymen who can't stand a woman interfering with
their ballgame experience.
</P>
<P>
   Wait 'til they find out that if the Giants aren't in contention
by midseason, Dusty Baker will be fired and replaced with Dianne
Feinstein.
</P>
<P>
   AND ONE PRAYER: That the Giants' new PA woman isn't one of those
hyperpeppy, gimmick-voiced, top-40 deejays who have taken over the
nation's ballpark PA systems and are holding the fans hostage. &QL; 
PHYSICS DEPT.: ``Just as a figure skater's rate of spin increases
when her arms are brought in close to the body,'' says Rod (Not &UR; the
 &LR; Rod Stewart) Stewart, ``the Earth may spin faster on its axis due
to deforestation. The cutting of tall trees may cause our planet to
spin dangerously fast.''
</P>
<P>
   Compelling theory. I think I've noticed a faster spin since Wilt
Chamberlain died.
</P>
<P>
   BURNING QUESTIONS: Why is it that in Southern California,
Yosemite is Yo-semite and in Northern California, it's You-semite?
</P>
<P>
   What ever happened to rack-and-pinion steering?
</P>
</TEXT>
