<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    AFC Capsule for Saturday, January 8, 2000
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Bills at Titans,
</P>
<P>
   12:30 p.m.,
</P>
<P>
   Saturday, ABC
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Where: Adelphia Coliseum, Nashville.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Records: Bills, 11-5 (second AFC wild card); Titans, 13-3
(first AFC wild card).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Series: Titans lead 22-15.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Last meeting: Titans won 31-14 (as the Oilers) in Memphis on
Nov. 23, 1997.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Outlook: This could be the most intriguing first-round match.
The Titans won four games in a row to finish 13-3 and won all eight
home games in their first season with a new stadium and new name.
The Bills have won three in a row, including a 31-6 pasting of the
AFC East champion Colts on Sunday. The Bills, who were 5-3 on the
road this season, might have a quarterback controversy. Backup Rob
Johnson, who was injured and lost his job to Doug Flutie last year,
passed for 287 yards and two touchdowns to snap the Colts' 11-game
winning streak. Bills' coach Wade Phillips said Flutie will start
at Tennessee. The Titans are on a roll offensively, averaging more
than 34 points in their past four games
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
