<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    AFC capsules for Sunday, January 9, 2000
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dolphins at Seahawks,
</P>
<P>
   4:05 p.m.,
</P>
<P>
   Sunday, CBS
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Where: Kingdome, Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Records: Dolphins, 9-7 (third AFC wild card); Seahawks, 9-7
(AFC West champs).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Series: Dolphins lead 4-2.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Last meeting: Seahawks won 22-15 in Miami on Oct. 6, 1996.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Outlook: On paper, this game, the last one ever in the
Kingdome, figures to be the worst first-round match. Both teams
backed into the playoffs after losing five of their last six games.
The Dolphins had made the playoffs before they kicked off on
Sunday, after Seattle lost to the New York Jets 19-9 at the
Meadowlands. The Seahawks thought they were eliminated, but then
Kansas City blew a fourth-quarter lead to Oakland and lost in
overtime. That gave Seattle the AFC West title and the third seed
in the playoffs. There will be some intriguing story lines. Is this
Dan Marino's final game? Will Jimmy Johnson return next season?
</P>
