<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NFC CAPSULE FOR SATURDAY, JANUARY 8, 2000
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Lions at Redskins,
</P>
<P>
   4:05 p.m.,
</P>
<P>
   Saturday, ABC
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Where: Redskins Stadium, Landover, Md.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Records: Lions, 8-8 (third NFC wild card); Redskins, 10-6 (NFC
East champions).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Series: Redskins lead 24-9.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Last meeting: Lions won 33-17 in Detroit on Dec. 5.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Outlook: The Redskins may have drawn the easiest first-round
game, as the Lions have lost four games in a row and may be without
starting quarterback Charlie Batch. Detroit, playing without
retired running back Barry Sanders for the first time since 1988,
opened the season 6-2 under head coach Bobby Ross. But the Lions
lost six of their final eight games to finish 8-8. Batch, a
second-year pro, made only two starts since Nov. 7 after breaking
his right thumb. Batch reinjured the thumb in Sunday's 24-17 loss
at Minnesota. Until losing at Detroit in December, the Redskins had
won 18 in a row against the Lions. Washington is making its first
playoff appearance since January 1993.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
