   ARTS/ENTERTAINMENT
</P>
<P>
   TV-MALCOLM _ Review of ``Malcolm in the Middle,'' quirky new Fox
sitcom that starts Sunday, and is technically the last new fall
show to debut. (Jubera, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   CAVEMAN-REVIEW _ Review of Rob Becker's one-man comedy
``Defending the Caveman,'' about the give and take, yin and yang,
tug and tussle between men and women. (Green, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   GAMESHOWS _ Here come the TV game shows. ``Winning Lines''
(hosted by Dick Clark) debuts Jan. 8 on CBS, ``Twenty One'' debuts
Jan. 9 on NBC, and ``Millionaire'' returns as a regular series on
Jan. 11, joining ``Greed,'' which continues on Fox. This can be
either a quick, bulleted story, or a long analysis of why this? why
now? depending on what editors want and how press tour shakes out.
(Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 25. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   GAMESHOWS-TIMELINE _ A timeline of game shows through the years.
(Jubera, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 10. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CHARLOTTE-ARTS _ CHARLOTTE, N.C. _ Through the leadership of
Charlotte's corporate community, art is blooming on an 11-block
stretch downtown. Fancy lobbies and chic restaurants beckon from
wide promenades. There's little retail yet, but with almost 8,000
people living in the vicinity, the stage is set. Folks in Charlotte
say it's all thanks to Hugh MColl, the Chief Executive Officer of
Bank of America. (Fox, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 24. WITH
PHOTO. EMBARGOED FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   DIRECTOR-JEWISON _ ATLANTA _ Movie director Norman Jewison has
never championed the populist, sure-to-make-money film. ``In The
Heat of the Night,'' ``Fiddler On The Roof,'' ``Moonstruck.'' His
are quality films, and often Oscar winners. This month, his ``The
Hurricane,'' starring Denzel Washington, has opened in metro
Atlanta and it's a role of such drama and power it could bring the
actor another Oscar nomination. We interview Jewison, who recently
visted Atlanta, about the making of ``The Hurricane,'' based on the
real life saga of Rubin ``Hurricane'' Carter, the boxing phenom
wrongly imprisoned for two decades on a false murder charge.
(BLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35. WITH PHOTO. EMBARGOED
FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   JEWISON-LIST _A list of films by Norman Jewison, director of
``The Hurricane.''(BLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 11.
EMBARGOED FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   SALESMAN _ A review of the Showtime production of ``Death of a
Salesman.'' (Hulbert, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16. EMBARGOED
FOR SUNDAY
</P>
