<P>
   DIRECTOR-JEWISON _ ATLANTA _ Movie director Norman Jewison has
never championed the populist, sure-to-make-money film. ``In The
Heat of the Night,'' ``Fiddler On The Roof,'' ``Moonstruck.'' His
are quality films, and often Oscar winners. This month, his ``The
Hurricane,'' starring Denzel Washington, has opened in metro
Atlanta and it's a role of such drama and power it could bring the
actor another Oscar nomination. We interview Jewison, who recently
visted Atlanta, about the making of ``The Hurricane,'' based on the
real life saga of Rubin ``Hurricane'' Carter, the boxing phenom
wrongly imprisoned for two decades on a false murder charge.
(BLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35. WITH PHOTO. EMBARGOED
