<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WATER-FILTERS-$ADV09-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     FILTERS MAY CUT COST OF DRINKING WATER WHILE IMPROVING TASTE 
</HEADLINE>
  
 &HT;     (For release Sunday, Jan. 9)   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By FRANCES INGRAHAM HEINS  
 &HT;     c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ If you have been investing in bottled water, you
may be able to reduce expenses by using a water filter to make your
water taste mountain fresh.
</P>
<P>
   The average person needs two quarts of water per day, but many
of us fall short.
</P>
<P>
   Water filters can be costly to install in your home and not an
option if you rent an apartment.
</P>
<P>
   Water filtration pitchers, such as those by Brita or Pur,
improve the taste and quality of household tap water.
</P>
<P>
   Brita says its water filtration pitcher reduces 99 percent of
chlorine (which can impair taste and odor), lead, bad tastes, odor,
copper and water hardness (as well as the chalky, scale buildup in
appliances) at a fraction of the cost of bottled water. A
replacement filter costs less than 20 cents per gallon of water
purified.
</P>
<P>
   It will not remove microbes or disinfect water that hasn't been
sufficiently treated. Those who require water of special purity
should follow the advice of a doctor or local health official.
</P>
<P>
   Filtered water is not recommended for fish, as some fish are
very sensitive to silver and/or changes in pH, but it can be used
on plants and flowers. The water pitcher filtration system also
softens tap water without adding sodium.
</P>
<P>
   It works like this: The upper tier of the pitcher holds tap
water until it flows through a carbon and resin filter, which it
houses in a reservoir between the top and filtered water in the
base.
</P>
<P>
   Filtering one quart of water takes approximately three to five
minutes. If your water is hard, or contains sediment and particles,
the filter should be changed more frequently.
</P>
<P>
   Brita water pitchers, which cost $26, and replacement filters
($7.99 for a single filter or $19.99 for a three pack), can be
found in grocery, drug, discount, health food, department, hardware
and warehouse club stores.
</P>
<P>
   Pur's product costs are similar.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
