   PEACE-TALKS (Shepherdstown, W.Va.) _ President Clinton returns
to peace talks and gives Israel and Syria a ``working document'' in
attempt to speed up sluggish negotiations. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   FED-SPENDING (Undated) _ Nineteen states paid billions more in
federal taxes than they received in federal aid, but Texans came
pretty close to breaking even, according to an annual from
Harvard's Kennedy School of Government. We look at the range of big
spenders and big payers, what federal dollars buy in Texas, and
some policy questions about how to equitably split money among the
states. By KIM COBB.
