have in custody another train-riding serial killer. The man charged
in the death of a 13-year-old girl and the attempted murder of a
10-year-old, has confessed to slayings in Kentucky, Alabama,
Arkansas, California and North Carolina. By JAMES PINKERTON.
</P>
<P>
   KLAN-TROOPER (Houston) _ A second black Texas trooper who worked
at the office in Livingston says he was given a Ku Klux Klan
birthday party after one month on the job. Trooper Robert Johnson,
who now works in Tyler, claims he took it as a joke, although in
hindsight he concedes it probably wasn't ``in good taste.'' By
JAMES KIMBERLY.
</P>
<P>
   TIGER-TOOTH (San Francisco) _ Tony the tiger might not have felt
``grrrrrrrrrreat`` after getting a root canal at the San Francisco
Zoo hospital, but he is sure to feel better soon. The 7-year-old,
380-pound Siberian tiger broke his lower left canine tooth,
prompting the zoo's veterinarians to operate. By ANASTASIA HENDRIX.
</P>
<P>
   MISSING-CHILD (Vallejo, Calif.) _ Investigators are combing a
vast landfill along the border of Washington and Oregon in search
of the body of a 7-year-old California girl who has been missing
since Dec. 9. By RYAN KIM.
</P>
