   BUSINESS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTER-COLUMN (Houston) _ If you are one of the many who found
a new computer under the Christmas tree, and that shiny new PC was
bought from a retailer, chances are you got a lot more than you
bargained for. Just look at all the icons in what is called the
system tray. The makers of these computers will tell you that these
programs _ and some hidden ones _ add features that you will like.
But what they won't tell you is that they can slow down a PC's
performance, conflict with other programs and possibly make your
computing life a living hell. By DWIGHT SILVERMAN.
</P>
