<TEXT>
<P>
   GEORGIA-GRAHAM-MCCAIN. As a John McCain supporter, how important
is Rep. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., to the would-be president's
campaign, especially considering the importance of the South
Carolina primary to McCain's uphill battle against George W. Bush
for the Republican nomination? (600-700 words.) By Elizabeth Hurt
</P>
<P>
   INDIANA-TELECOMMUTE. Just one year ago, Capitol Hill lawmakers
were deciding whether to impeach President Clinton, one of the most
watched events of the 1990s. The tamer issue these days is safety
in home offices. (500 words.) By Tania Anderson
</P>
