   SMALL BUSINESS-NASA. NASA announced Thursday 25 small businesses
in 12 states have been awarded an estimated $15 million to carry on
with research that the agency is interested in using on future
missions. (500 words.) By Laura J. Winter
</P>
<P>
   SMALL BUSINESS-WAGE. President Clinton unveiled his domestic
agenda for 2000 this week, including a push to increase the minimum
wage, a measure that fell short of full passage by the end of last
year. (500 words.) By Jonathan Lipman
</P>
<P>
   SPACE-PHONES. Satellite phones, a technology long heralded as
the future in mobile communications but slow to pan out, are
finally available to the public on a limited basis at an affordable
level. Globalstar USA announced commercial service and a pricing
plan Friday. (500 words.) By Jonathan Lipman
</P>
<P>
   WYOMING-RACE. Although the presidential election is almost a
year away, Wyoming residents say dueling candidates for the
nation's top slot are making their presence known for better or for
worse (550 words.)
</P>
<P>
   -30-
