<P>
   FBN-AFC-LEDE _ Once again, the-little-QB-who-could is in the eye
of a storm. The Bills wanted to rest starter Doug Flutie last week
to keep him healthy and give Rob Johnson a chance to play. The move
backfired. Johnson had one of his best performances ever, creating
a playoff-eve QB controversy. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFC-LEDE _ History suggests that Detroit will make a quick
exit from the playoffs today. The Lions haven't won in Washington
since 1968, a string of 17 straight losses. And players are aware
of the history. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-MARINO _ And so after nearly 17 seasons, it has come to
this: Dan Marino, the most productive passer in NFL history, being
mentioned in the same breath as Johnny Unitas, Joe Namath, Y.A.
Tittle. Only these days, the 38-year-old Marino is conjuring up
images of a sorry sort: A 40-year-old Unitas getting sacked on his
final play. A battered Broadway Joe hobbling off the field in a
Rams uniform. Tittle, on his knees, blood dripping from his face.
(Capozza, Palm Beach Post). 32. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFL-EUROPE _ IRVING, Texas _ On a rare day off, Brandon
Noble would sit on his hotel balcony in northern Spain, wondering
if the NFL was on his horizon. The beautiful scenery surrounding
the tiny town of Sitges, a suburb of Barcelona, is a perfect
honeymoon destination, but in the spring of 1999, Noble was on a
business trip. He was a defensive tackle for the Barcelona Dragons,
a charter member of NFL Europe, so the nearby Mediterranean beaches
and old Spanish castles had to wait. ``I lived in a little resort
area for two springs,'' Noble said during a break from practice
this week. ``The first year I took in all the sites. The second
year I really was more wrapped up in football.'' For Noble and
hundreds of other football players, NFL Europe is a breeding ground
for future NFL prospects. Players who live in Barcelona or
Frankfurt or Berlin aspire to catch the attention of scouts from
Dallas, Green Bay or Kansas City. (Cantu, Austin
American-Statesman). 20-24.
</P>
<P>
   MADONNA-SUPERBOWL _ Short story sharing details of Madonna's
Super Bowl pregame gig in Atlanta. (Longino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
