dealership floor. Some of them look flat-out uncomfortable to
drive. But half the fun of going to an exhibit like the Greater Los
Angeles Auto Show which opens this weekend is gawking at the
concept cars. A dozen make their world or North American debut in
Los Angeles this weekend, including the Honda Sprocket, Saturn CV1
Concept and Ford Mustang Concept. By Greg Wilcox (Will move on the
``n'' California, ``a'' national and ``f'' financial news wires.)
