skyrocketing this week, with premiums for some businesses rising 18
to 25 percent. Industry officials say it's just a change in the way
they do business because in the last few years they were
underpricing the rates to increase market share. Checking to see if
new laws also impacted industry. By Dereck Andrade (Will move on
the ``n'' California, ``a'' national and ``f'' financial news
wires.)
