   ECON-REPORT (Washington) _ Employers added jobs at a
surprisingly robust rate in December, propelling the economy into
the new year with considerable momentum, the Labor Department
reports. And while there was good news across the board, the
figures substantially increased the likelihood that the Federal
Reserve will act to keep the economy from overheating by raising
interest rates next month. By Richard W. Stevenson.
