   Top center story:
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-CHECHNYA (Mozdok, Russia) _ Confronted with fierce rebel
resistance, rising casualties and bad weather, the Russian military
announces it is suspending its assault on Grozny, the Chechen
capital. Lt. Gen. Gennady Troshev said the pause is intended to
allow the thousands of civilians still trapped in Grozny to escape
from the fighting. He did not say how long it will last. By Michael
R. Gordon. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
1,200 words.
