r e BC-JEWISON-LIST09-COX     01-07 0383
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JEWISON-LIST09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The Norman Jewison video file
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Dec. 9.
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Other People's Money'' (1991; R) _ The off-Broadway hit
comedy about the greed of the '80s dies on the big screen.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``In Country'' (1989; R) _ Bruce Willis proved he could act
long before ``The Sixth Sense'' with this touching homage to
Vietnam veterans.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Moonstruck'' (1987; PG) _ Cher won an Oscar as the very
Italian woman caught in a love triangle with Nicolas Cage.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Agnes of God'' (1985; PG-13) _ Based on the play about a nun
who apparently got pregnant and killed the baby, it features three
solid performances from Anne Bancroft, Jane Fonda and Meg Tilly.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``A Soldier's Story'' (1984; PG) _ A gripping World War II
whodunit about the murder of a black officer at a Southern military
post.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``... And Justice for All'' (1979; R) _ Al Pacino and the
whole out-of-order legal system jockey in this wicked satire.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``F.I.S.T.'' (1978; PG) _ Sylvester Stallone in a tale of a
labor kingpin that was an instant F.L.O.P.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Rollerball'' (1975; R) _ Sports violence that predates TV's
``American Gladiators.'' And just as sad.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Jesus Christ Superstar'' (1973; G) _ The ultimate rock
opera. Guess you had to be there.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Fiddler on the Roof'' (1971; G) _ A lavish, expertly
directed musical. Won Oscars for cinematography and scoring.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Thomas Crown Affair'' (1968; R) _ Steve McQueen and Faye
Dunaway defined cool in this elaborate bank heist flick.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``In the Heat of the Night'' (1967; PG) _ Rod Steiger won an
Oscar as the Mississippi cop investigating a murder with a visiting
Northeast detective (Sidney Poitier) in this best picture winner.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Russians Are Coming! The Russians Are Coming!'' (1966;
unrated) _ Cold-war funny business as a Soviet sub runs aground at
Martha's Vineyard.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Send Me No Flowers'' (1964; unrated) _ One of the goofy
Doris Day-Rock Hudson comedies.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Forty Pounds of Trouble'' (1963; unrated) _ Tony Curtis is
the casino manager stuck with a precocious little girl.
</P>
<P>
   _Bob Longino writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
