Dramatically, Ms. Valayre makes a lovely, vulnerable and, as the
tragedy unfolds, impassioned Cio-Cio-San. Her singing is confident
and often striking. (Sara Krulwich/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) NEW YORK -- Jan. 7, 2000 -- STERN-GERMANY -- Fritz Stern
is a Columbia University historian who has become a trusted
external judge of Germany's bitter internal debates on its history
and its new role in the world. ``I am a full-blooded non-Aryan,''
he says. ``Of course, I am completely of Jewish descent. But my
stumbling block with the description of myself as a Jewish
historian is that it was Hitler that decided I was a Jew.''
(Vincent Laforet/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
