<SLUG> BC-GEN-CSUNNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BIG WEST COUNCIL TO DISCUSS ADDING NORTHRIDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Big West Council meets Sunday in San Diego,
and the possibility of adding Cal State Northridge as a future
member will be discussed, Big West Commissioner Dennis Farrell
said.
</P>
<P>
   Farrell said the council won't vote to include CSUN or UC
Riverside in a future expansion, though.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not going to take a formal vote on this, only because it
would be a straw poll,'' Farrell said. ``Until our presidents vote
on it, I don't want to have the chance of those two bodies be
placed at odds with each other. We're going to discuss expansion
and discuss candidates ... then see where we go from there.''
</P>
<P>
   CSUN, a member of the Big Sky Conference, is an affiliate member
of the Big West in softball and will join the conference in
baseball in 2001.
</P>
<P>
   The Big West is losing Nevada and Boise State as full-time
members next year and New Mexico State and North Texas have asked
to leave, as well.
</P>
<P>
   Lineman transfers: Tim Shoffeitt, a sophomore offensive lineman
who started all 22 games he played in for the Cal State Northridge
football team, is transferring to Azusa Pacific.
</P>
<P>
   CSUN coach Jeff Kearin said Shoffeitt told him his plans Friday
morning. Shoffeitt, 6-foot-1 and 290 pounds, made the Big Sky
Conference All-Academic team as a freshman.
</P>
<P>
   Shoffeitt's departure means Ashcon Madjid, a freshman from L.A.
Baptist High who redshirted last season, moves to the top of the
depth chart at right guard.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
