<SLUG> BC-FBN-REDSKINS-LIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE HIGHWAY TO SUCCESS LEADS A COACH ASTRAY 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 By MIKE FREEMAN    
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   When Mike Nolan, the defensive coordinator of the Washington
Redskins, held the same position with the Giants from 1993-96, some
people in the team's front office thought that one day Nolan would
be a head coach. A few other teams felt the same way. Nolan
appeared to be on the fast track for stardom.
</P>
<P>
   Then Dan Reeves was fired as the Giants' head coach, and instead
of waiting to see if Reeves would catch on elsewhere, Nolan took
the sure thing; he went to Washington as an assistant under Coach
Norv Turner.
</P>
<P>
   It is a decision that Nolan may regret. If he had waited and
gone to the Atlanta Falcons with Reeves, Nolan would have coached
in a Super Bowl, and his job would now be secure. He would not be
waiting for his fate to be decided by ownership the way it is in
Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Quite simply, if Nolan's defense, which has struggled in his
tenure as the defensive coordinator with the Redskins, does not
perform well in the postseason, Nolan will most likely be fired.
</P>
<P>
   The Redskins play their first-round National Football Conference
playoff game against Detroit at home Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   If Washington is to beat the Lions, the defense must play better
than when the two teams met in Detroit earlier this season and the
Redskins lost, 33-17. That snapped Washington's 18-0 winning streak
_ including two playoff games _ against Detroit. But still hanging
over Detroit is the fact that the Lions are 0-17 on the road
against the Redskins since the franchise moved to Washington in
1937.
</P>
<P>
   Nolan told reporters this week that he was not concerned about
his status and that his only job was to help the team win. ``That's
all I'm thinking about now,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   The Redskins are one of the most intriguing teams in the
playoffs. Every step of the way, the owner Daniel Snyder hovers
over the franchise. No one has felt Snyder's heat more than Nolan
and his defense. At least once Snyder has called for Nolan to be
fired, with Turner intervening to save Nolan's job.
</P>
<P>
   Washington finished the regular season with the NFL's
30th-ranked defense, ahead of only the expansion Cleveland Browns.
Washington gave up 27.8 points, 402.3 total yards and 127.4 yards
rushing a game through its first eight games. The team improved in
its last eight, giving up 19.4 points, 310.9 total yards and 119.3
yards on the ground a game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think they have a fine defense,'' Coach Bobby Ross of the
Lions said.
</P>
<P>
   What Ross truly has to worry about is Washington's offense. The
Redskins scored 443 points this season, second only to St. Louis,
which scored 526. This was the team that scored 50 points against
the Giants.
</P>
<P>
   So Detroit, to have a chance, must score at least three
touchdowns, and that will only keep the Lions close to the
Redskins. What will make that harder for Detroit is the return of
Redskins runner Stephen Davis, who missed the final two
regular-season games with a sprained ankle.
</P>
<P>
   Davis, who is listed as probable but will start the game even
though he will not be 100 percent, rushed for 1,405 yards and 17
touchdowns during the season.
</P>
<P>
   A victory for the Redskins and a good performance by the defense
means Nolan, as well as the rest of the defensive staff, will
probably return. But more important, a victory puts Washington a
step closer to the Super Bowl.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
